history.content:
Same situation. I got added into some of them. 

It might help to clarify which classes you are currently waitlisted for but one thing that might helpful to look at would be to check the classes themselves to see if they have room. It might be that the discussion (in my case EE16B lab) is full and thus you are kept on the waitlist.

Definitely do not drop and re-enroll. It won't help.

Please keep in mind that there are a LOT of EECS majors. If you are newly declared, you are wait listed because the reserved seats are already full. If/when more seats become available during Phase 1 or 2 for your reserve cap, you will be given access to those seats based on your wait list order. (The enrollment system first considers whether you meet reserve requirements and then processes by wait list order within that group.) 

Once the adjustment period begins, the wait lists are process in sequential order - regardless of major.

Hi, I recently switched to EECS, and am on the waitlist for a bunch of classes I didn't meet the reserve cap for, but now do. Should I drop and re-add these classes to get put into the class instantly, or will it eventually happen?
history.subject: Enrollment in Waitlisted Classes after Declaring
